<div id="review_585150069" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/585150069" />
    <a title="Jonfaith" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2327886-jonfaith"><img alt="Jonfaith" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1534772484p2/2327886.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/585150069?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jonfaith" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jonfaith" href="/user/show/2327886-jonfaith">Jonfaith</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780061120152" href="/book/show/126576.Under_the_Volcano">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer585150069" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9305747737792981065">Towards the nightmarish conclusion of Under the Volcano, Yvonne recognizes that the drinks &quot;lay like swine on her soul.&quot; That poetic glimpse into Bacchic darkness is a glimpse of the novel&apos;s mastery, It is impossible to distinguish it only as a novel about alcoholism, or, even, a return to the primoridal Eden besieged by History&apos;s jackboots. Under the Volcano is so much more than that. Each of the principal characters exposes their soul, yet motivations remain dim, much like the fetid cantinas a</span>
  <span id="freeText9305747737792981065" style="display:none">Towards the nightmarish conclusion of Under the Volcano, Yvonne recognizes that the drinks "lay like swine on her soul." That poetic glimpse into Bacchic darkness is a glimpse of the novel's mastery, It is impossible to distinguish it only as a novel about alcoholism, or, even, a return to the primoridal Eden besieged by History's jackboots. Under the Volcano is so much more than that. Each of the principal characters exposes their soul, yet motivations remain dim, much like the fetid cantinas and the dubious mescal.<br /><br />The novel's poetry is electrically animated and emerges from the pages like Promethean firestorms. Pedestrian brains will find themselves winded and unnerved by the pyrotechnics. I know I was. Consider me grateful for such. </span>
  <a data-text-id="9305747737792981065" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


